title: Fortran Programs for Chemical Process Design, Analysis, and Simu
description:
Fortran Programs for Chemical Process Design, Analysis, and Simulation - A. Kayode Coker (Elsevier, 1995).pdf

ISBN 0884152804

Now engineers can solve process design problems with their own personal computers using FORTRAN language without having to rely on expensive computer packages that often are limited in scope and do not meet the requirements of the project. The fundamental theories, equations and computer programs in this book provide a ready way to analyze and solve a wide range of process design problems
